rComments: A brutally honest critic, but this quality ultimately and effectively pushes students towards clear and resolved presentation of ideas, improving their quality of work. However harsh, he clearly cares a lot about his students, and is eager to listen to their ideas and approaches to creating and learning. I learned a lot from him.

I don't think he is a bad professor, just has too high of expectations, especially for a second year course. He is good at getting the class engaged in a discussion, and ultimately does try to get the best out of students. However, I think academic resources were too limited for the class as well: too much expected given the materials we received.

A brilliant instructor but also a harsh grader. Be prepared for the projects & critiques cuz he is expecting a lot from you.

Gareth is a tough critic & expects good participation during critique, which may or may not be critiqued itself. However harsh at times, it made me understand the importance of clean presentation, confidence and clarity when sharing and speaking about my work; his high standards pushed me to create works that were meaningful and refined.

Rough... Marks hard. Way to focused on specifics and wants all work to be way too literal for viewers to feel intellectually engaged with it all. He responds to emails by the next day usually so thats nice
